<div id="review_5738936" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/5738936" />
    <a title="JG (Introverted Reader)" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/48404-jg-introverted-reader"><img alt="JG (Introverted Reader)" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1327259536p2/48404.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/5738936?book_show_action=true">Sep 05, 2007</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="JG (Introverted Reader)" class="user" itemprop="url" name="JG (Introverted Reader)" href="/user/show/48404-jg-introverted-reader">JG (Introverted Reader)</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/48404-jg-introverted-reader?shelf=reviewed">reviewed</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/48404-jg-introverted-reader?shelf=womens_fiction">womens_fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/48404-jg-introverted-reader?shelf=3_stars">3_stars</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/48404-jg-introverted-reader?shelf=z_read_in_2007">z_read_in_2007</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/48404-jg-introverted-reader?shelf=gave_away">gave_away</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/48404-jg-introverted-reader?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer5738936" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4227168754666367577"><i>The Pilot&apos;s Wife</i> in a nutshell: Jack Lyons, a commercial pilot, is flying a plane when it explodes. The book follows the grieving process of his widow, as she tries to figure out what happened in that plane. The overriding question in the book is &quot;How well can we ever really know someone else?&quot;<br/><br/>There wasn&apos;t anything really wrong with the book, it was just overly gray for my taste. I don&apos;t think the sun shines in the entire book. It was solidly written though, and it did keep me turning pages. I d</span>
  <span id="freeText4227168754666367577" style="display:none"><i>The Pilot's Wife</i> in a nutshell: Jack Lyons, a commercial pilot, is flying a plane when it explodes. The book follows the grieving process of his widow, as she tries to figure out what happened in that plane. The overriding question in the book is "How well can we ever really know someone else?"<br /><br />There wasn't anything really wrong with the book, it was just overly gray for my taste. I don't think the sun shines in the entire book. It was solidly written though, and it did keep me turning pages. I did have a vague idea where the whole thing was going from about a third of the way through. I wasn't exactly right, but I was close.<br /><br />This really was not my kind of book. I have a feeling it would appeal to fans of Nicholas Sparks. In fact, my mom is a huge fan of his and I sent her this book to read today.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="4227168754666367577" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


